
Overview of noun crackle

The noun crackle has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (2) crackle, crackling, crepitation -- (the sharp sound of snapping noises)
2. crackle, crackleware, crackle china -- (glazed china with a network of fine cracks on the surface)

Overview of verb crackle

The verb crackle has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (2) crepitate, crackle -- (make a crackling sound; "My Rice Krispies crackled in the bowl")
2. (1) crunch, scranch, scraunch, crackle -- (make a crushing noise; "his shoes were crunching on the gravel")
3. (1) crackle -- (to become, or to cause to become, covered with a network of small cracks; "The blazing sun crackled the desert sand")

Overview of adj crackle

The adj crackle has 1 sense (no senses from tagged texts)
                                        
1. crackle -- (having the surface decorated with a network of fine cracks, as in crackleware; "a crackle glaze")
